Requirements

To use the Text-to-Speech functionality in this project, you need to have access to Google Cloud services. Specifically, the Google Cloud Text-to-Speech API is required.
Steps to Enable Google Cloud Text-to-Speech

    Create a Google Cloud Project:
        Go to the Google Cloud Console.
        Create a new project or use an existing one.

    Enable the Text-to-Speech API:
        In your Google Cloud project, navigate to APIs & Services > Library.
        Search for "Text-to-Speech API" and click Enable.

    Set Up Authentication:
        Go to APIs & Services > Credentials.
        Click on Create Credentials > Service Account.
        Download the generated JSON file and save it securely.

    Set the Environment Variable:
        Ensure your system can locate the authentication file by setting the GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS environment variable:

        export GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS="path/to/your/credentials-file.json"

        Replace path/to/your/credentials-file.json with the actual path to your JSON file.

Notes

    Billing Required: The Google Cloud Text-to-Speech API is not free. You need to have a billing account set up to use it.
    Ensure you monitor usage to avoid unexpected costs.